The Browns should, no, need to hire Tony Dungey, he has the mindset, maturity, stability, he's the guy who can change the culture of, divas immaturity, and most importantly LACK of Discipline that plagues the Browns organization.
I'd also trade Baker for a 1st round pick, and draft the best defensive player available.
Lastly a curve ball. I'd sign Tebow outta retirement, ( he's in shape, and tons of tread left on the tires) he's not the most accurate QB, but you dont have to be with Beckham and Jarvis, you already have Chubb, hunt, get a receiving TE in free agency.
Tebow, I believe, represents the attitude of selflessness, team first, hard nosed, blue collar lunch pail mentality needed in the position, and in AFC north. That would sell tickets, and change the mentality in Cleveland, Tebow is all heart, and Cleveland desperately needs leadership. It's crazy, crazy smart.
